thread.title: Big 7.0 quake strikes Indonesia

author: eTN Editor
title: Big 7.0 quake strikes Indonesia
text:
Big 7.0 quake strikes Indonesia Adv: 
Jul 27, 2015 Adv: 
A big 7.0 magnitude earthquake struck Papua, Indonesia, today, July 27, 2015, at 21:41:22 UTC. This comes one day after the same region was struck by a 6.7 quake. 
The quake occurred 110 kilometers south-southwest of the town of Kokopo, the US Geological Survey said, 689 kilometers northeast of the Pacific nation’s capital Port Moresby, in the New Britain region at a depth of 53 kilometers. 
There were no tsunami warnings, the Pacific Tsunami Warning Center said. 
Distances: 
• 234 km (145 mi) W of Abepura, Indonesia • 247 km (153 mi) W of Jayapura, Indonesia • 314 km (194 mi) W of Vanimo, Papua New Guinea • 341 km (211 mi) ENE of Nabire, Indonesia • 1195 km (740 mi) SSE of Koror Town, Palau
